==English==

===Etymology===
From [[Phoenician]], meaning ''mercy of [[Baal]]''. ([[w:Hannibal Barca|Hannibal Barca]]'s epithet, ''barca'', is Phoenician for ''[[lightning]]''; [[cf]] the [[Canaanite]] ''baraq''.)

===Proper noun===
{{en-proper noun}}
#{{given name|male|from Phoenician|}} A male [[given name]] meaning ''mercy of [[Baal]]''.
#{{historical}} Any of [[w:Hannibal (disambiguation)|several historical figures]], most notably the [[Carthaginian]] [[general]] [[w:Hannibal Barca|Hannibal Barca]].
# A [[city]] in [[Missouri]]: [[w:Hannibal, Missouri]].

